snippet: Nearly 100 passengers are thought to have died when a boat packed with refugees sank south of Indonesia this week, Australian officials said on Friday.
abstract: Australian officials say nearly 100 passengers are thought to have died when a boat packed with refugees sank south of Indonesia.
lead_paragraph: Nearly 100 passengers are thought to have died when a boat packed with refugees sank south of Indonesia this week, Australian officials said on Friday.

headline.seo: Nearly 100 Migrants Presumed Dead at Sea as Australia Ends Search
headline.main: Australia Ends Search in Boat Sinking With Scores Presumed Dead
headline.print_headline: Nearly 100 Migrants Are Presumed Dead at Sea, Australia Says
